{"word":"ἀναπείθω","slug":"ἀναπείθω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἀναπείϑω</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀνά\">ἀνά</a>, <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:πείθω\">πείθω</a></el>] ‘to encourage by persuasion’, <b><i>persuade.</i></b> In <b><a href='B:510 18:13'>Ac 18:13</a></b> <el>ἀ.</el> follows a phrase that questions the validity of the persuasion, hence the nuance <i>incite<b>.</b></i> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀναπαύω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀνάπειρος\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}